node.text: She made it 'Clap for Democracy' and encouraged us to #StopBeingPoor, now the 'Famously Iconic' @Ziwef is on to her next challenge, #SongAssociation. Watch on this episode as she sings Madonna, and discusses a range of topics, from middle school dance floors to the remake she'd love to star in.

node.text: ELLE.com here, your one and only source into the fabulous life of @WhitneyPeak, star of HBO Max’s @GossipGirl. Spotted on the July Digital Cover, she’s letting ELLE #AskMeAnything. Tune in as she dishes on her dream scene partner, her favorite OG 'Gossip Girl’ scene and the song that serves as her current theme song. XOXO. #GossipGirl

node.text: @MadisonBeer's must-haves for a relaxing day off? Sleeping in, sweats, and skincare galore. The singer/songwriter recently added co-founder to her résumé with the launch of her skincare line, #KNOWBeauty, and today she's showing it off to ELLE (along with a glimpse of her insane closet) on #WakingUpWith.

node.title: This Is Madison Beer's Morning Routine | Waking Up With

node.text: They may only be 6 months into their career, but the boys of @ENHYPEN aren't your average rookies. Tune in as they sing BTS, Lauv, and hits off their sophomore EP, #BORDERCARNIVAL in a race against our buzzer! #ENGENE

node.text: Country music sensation and ELLE cover star @spaceykacey is stepping in for #SongAssociation! The singer-songwriter is no stranger to a Grammy, and as we anxiously await her upcoming album, we're putting her music knowledge (and vocals!) to the test. Tune in as she sings Dua Lipa, talks working with Willie Nelson, and what to expect from her next album.

node.text: May cover star @OliviaRodrigo​ is taking the wheel on #SongAssociation​! The talented newcomer has become one of *the* biggest pop stars in the world, making history as both of her debut smash hits, #driverslicense​ and #dejavu​, sit at the top of the charts. Tune in on this episode as she sings #TaylorSwift​, dishes on her dream collaboration, her first concert, and the song she wishes she wrote.

node.text: The talented @ZaraLarsson​ is the #PosterGirl​ for a number of things, but most notably, her barrier-breaking, electro-pop hits. Out with her sophomore album, the multi-platinum artist returns for her second turn at #SongAssociation​. Tune in as she sings Ciara, Hailee Steinfeld, and her new release, “Look What You’ve Done”.

node.text: On September 11, 2001, journalists across the country took on the unimaginable: reporting on a series of terrorist attacks that would change America forever. Twenty years later, they’re opening up to ELLE about the stories of loss, love, and extraordinary heroism they worked so hard to tell. Pulitzer Prize-winning @nytimes photojournalist @fremson captured this startling image of a New York City firefighter and police officer at the Stage Door Deli in downtown Manhattan (slide 2) shortly after the Twin Towers fell. “It’s actually a beautiful, sunny day, so in theory it should be a gorgeous scene outside, but instead we’re in a cloud,” she says. “The only light was from the deli case that hadn’t been turned off. There was a weird glow, an awful green. Smoke started coming up from the basement, and at that point there was so much misinformation, nobody knew what was going on.” Click the link in bio for the full story. Photo 2 courtesy @nytimes, @reduxpictures, @fremson.
